<HL>
   Philippine Trade Deficit
</HL>
<DATE>
08/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   MANILA, the Philippines -- The Philippine trade deficit
widened 63% to $1.87 billion in the first half from $1.15
billion a year earlier, the National Statistics Office said.
   Exports rose 3.7% to $3.9 billion from $3.76 billion in
the first six months of 1989, while imports grew a hefty 18%
to $5.77 billion from $4.91 billion.
</LP>
