<HL>
   British Retail Sales Volume Rises
</HL>
<DATE>
08/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   LONDON -- Retail sales volume in Britain rose a
provisional 1.0% in July from June and was up 2.3% from July
1989, the U.K. Central Statistical Office said.
   Market forecasts for July were for a rise of 0.4% on the
month.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Retail sales volume was up 0.1% in the three months ended
in July, compared with the previous three months but was up
1.6% from a year earlier, the statistical office said.
   The value of retail sales was up about 9% in July from
July 1989.
</TEXT>
