   Dow Jones Index Changes
</HL>
<DATE>
08/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C6
</SO>
<CO>
   SIX GRL HON
</CO>
<IN>
STOCK INDEXES (NDX)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Several changes are being made in the industry
groups of the Dow Jones Equity Market index, all effective
today.
   General Instrument Corp. is being removed from the
communication technology group because it is being acquired,
and is being replaced by Scientific-Atlanta Inc.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Honeywell Inc. is being moved to the electronic components
industry group from the diversified technology group, and
Acuson Corp. is being moved to the medical and biotechnology
industry group from the medical supplies group. Both changes
were made to better reflect the two companies' businesses.
   Motel 6 L.P. is being removed from the lodging industry
group because it is being acquired.
