<LP>
   Tacoma, Wash. -- Weyerhaeuser Co. said trading in its
stock was halted after it notified shareholders and stock
exchanges of its program to swap $2.625 convertible
exchangeable preference shares for a new issue of $200
million principal amount of 5 1/4% convertible debentures due
2017.
   Effective Sept. 15, preference shareholders of record Aug.
10 are to receive $1,000 pricipal amount of the debentures in
exchange for 20 preference shares held. Shareholders will
receive an amount equal to the dividend of 65.625 cents a
share accruing to Sept. 15, 1990, the company added.
Alternatively, the preference shares may be converted into
common at a rate of 1.0416 common shares a preference share.
