</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FLR MOB WE T.W
</CO>
<LP>
   IRVINE, Calif. -- Fluor Corp., an engineering,
construction, and technical services concern, said that it
was awarded two contracts valued at $22 million.
   Fluor said that its Fluor Daniel unit was awarded a
contract by Vancouver-based Westcoast Energy Inc. for $10
million to provide process design, detailed engineering and
procurement for expansion of a gas processing facility near
Fort St. John, in northeast British Columbia. Project
completion is scheduled for late 1991.
