   Who's News:
   McDonnell Douglas
   Names David Little
   To C-17 Program
</HL>
<DATE>
08/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2
</SO>
<CO>
   WNEWS MD
</CO>
<LP>
   LONG BEACH, Calif. -- McDonnell Douglas Corp.'s Douglas
Aircraft Co. division named David A. Little vice
president-deputy general manager of its C-17 military cargo
plane program, in further executive shuffling designed to
shore up performance on the Air Force contract.
   Mr. Little, 47 years old, previously general manager of
the program, succeeds Jack Hayden, 43, who assumed the newly
created post of vice president-deputy general manager for
fiscal management and support.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Little will concentrate on manufacturing operations,
and will work with Leonard F. Impellizzeri, staff vice
president for engineering and advanced systems for the St.
Louis-based parent who in May was named vice president-deputy
general manager of the C-17, with responsibility for
technical aspects of the program.
