   Fujitsu Ltd. (Japan) -- $330 million of bonds due Aug. 30,
1994, with equity-purchase warrants, indicating a 5% coupon
at par, via Nikko Securities Co. Each $10,000 bond carries
two warrants, exercisable from Sept. 19, 1990, through Aug.
9, 1994, to buy company shares at an expected premium of 2
1/2% to the closing share price when terms are fixed Friday.
   Chujitsuya Co. (Japan) -- 120 million Swiss francs ($91.3
million) of 7 3/4% public bonds in two tranches. First
tranche of 70 million Swiss francs issued at 100 1/2,
maturing Sept. 5, 1997, guaranteed by Yokohama Bank. Second
tranche of 50 million Swiss francs is issued at 100 3/8,
maturing Sept. 5, 1995, guaranteed by Fuji Bank.
   Deutsche Bank Finance N.V., (West German parent) -- 100
million Australian dollars (US$79.8 million) of 14% bonds due
Sept. 7, 1993, priced at 100.95 to yield 14.24% less fees via
Deutsche Bank Capital Markets Ltd. Guaranteed by Deutsche
Bank AG. Fees 1 1/2.
   ANZ Banking Group (Australia) -- 75 million Australian
dollars of 14 3/4% bonds due Sept. 20, 1993, priced at 101.95
to yield 14.55% less fees via Samuel Montagu &amp; Co. Fees 1
1/2.
